<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: TOPIC: MIN PVP LVL</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Vlar">Vlar</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:07 p.m. 15/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: TOPIC: MIN PVP LVL<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=907" TARGET=_self>TOPIC: MIN PVP LVL</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Well we had a discussion of sorts awhile back and Senior Guide Majara had an idea that could limit newbie killing, at least in the batyards.

<P>She said to put a few wandering guards that do not hunt npc's just kinda of like a policing system in the newbie areas. If you had 4 - 5 of these types of guards (with good sized hate radius) you could prevent most people from getting pk'ed in the newbie area.
<P>Also as for the level limit that has been discussed. I think that the level limit should go along with the experience used for npc's. As you progress higher you range that you can kill npc's increases so when you are in the 20's you can kill +-6 and in the mid 30's kill +-10 etc.
<P>Thoughts,
<P>Vlar
<P>&gt; We have had numerous complaints about Newbie killing and In race
<BR>&gt; newbie killing. What can we do to fix this problem so that when
<BR>&gt; a new person to the PvP server comes on the PvP server they
<BR>&gt; don't get discourage by getting killed immediately.
<P>&gt; Do we need a min PvP lvl? (I.E. Can't PvP or be PvPed until LVL
<BR>&gt; 4)
<P>&gt; Do we need something else? If so What?
<P>&gt; If you think it should stay the way it is, Why?
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
